                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.01/99</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-15T20:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1916, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Bitter factional struggle Kwangtung; Chekiang quiet. In Peking Vice President and
                    Yuan cooperate. They contemplate joint action. Governors asking the President to
                    withdraw. The latter is looking for suitable man to form coalition Cabinet, thus
                    far in vain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
